latestIgtvVideos.title: Wavy hair styling routine for beginners
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Raking never worked for me! It gave me stringy hair, ruined my thick clumps, gave me less definition and shrinkage.😵

However, I might revisit raking once I feel my wave pattern is stronger. 💪
Especially for beginners when your hair is learning how to fall into its natural shape, raking does not help! 💁‍♀️
 
I feel that raking suits curly hair more because their hair pattern is strong enough to shrink back whereas for waves it just elongates them. This is just my opinion if you are a wavy and raking suits you, great! Keep doing what is best for YOUR HAIR! 💯

Praying hands reduce frizz and help form clumps and scrunching enhances wave formation✨ 

Water is essential for styling hair, you can see the difference between less water and more water in my highlight ‘styling’ 

I have learned all this about raking and use of water in styling and a lot more from @powerdomi 

Also, these two products from @fiixmycurls are perfect for beginners, they are easy to use and there isn't much of a learning curve with these babies ❤️ 

You can achieve great results from just one use if you keep a few things in your mind which I have talked about in my review of these products. You will find it in my highlight names ‘reviews’

Is this the routine that you follow? If not, do try this routine and tell me if it suits you or not!❤️

Both of them are available on the @vanitywagon  website. Use code NERDYWAVES for a 20% discount!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Styling my mom’s hair
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
My mom’s hair has gone through severe chemical damage. 3 times rebonding, 2 times smoothening and 1-time keratin is a lot for the hair to handle. She did all of that to tame the frizz and to look professional which is a common stereotype that only straight hair looks professional.

I was able to convince her to adopt cgm. It has been 3 months and there is an improvement, still a long way to go. I cut her straight ends a month ago, still, some are left and I will be doing it again soon.

Her hair always felt rough to touch even on washdays but today for the first time it felt so soft. THANKS TO @flawsomeofficial  kinky berries hair mask. 
She wrapped a warm towel around her head for 45 mins for deeper conditioning. 

I styled her hair upside because she has spondylitis.
You can see the stylers I used and the quantity. @fiixmycurls  and @letscurlupdotcom 

The technique used for applying leave-in cream is raking with scrunching, and for gel roping, glazing and scrunching again. 

I am thinking of getting olaplex for her ✨
